The paper deals with the economics of cybercrime markets and the trading of exploits, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the production and deployment of attack technologies, which could be classified under software engineering (cs.SE). The use of market factors to predict the likelihood of exploit deployment could be considered a topic in cybernetics (cs.CY) or systems and control (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the measurement of exploits, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) if the measurement involves analyzing the behavior of malware.
